      <h1>Understanding the New Digital SAT: Format, Scoring, and Prep Tips</h1>
      <p class="article-intro">The SAT underwent its most significant transformation in decades when College Board transitioned the test from paper to digital in March 2024 for US students. The new digital SAT is shorter, adaptive, and structurally different from the test that millions of students took for nearly a century. Whether you are a student preparing for the test, a parent trying to understand the changes, or an educator adjusting your curriculum, this guide covers everything you need to know about the digital SAT — from the adaptive format and scoring system to the most effective preparation strategies. Use our <a href="/education-calculators/sat-score-calculator/">SAT score calculator</a> to estimate your composite score and see how it compares to national percentiles.</p>
    </header>

