    <p>The Reading and Writing section tests four main content areas: Craft and Structure (about 28 percent of questions), which covers vocabulary in context, text structure, and purpose; Information and Ideas (about 26 percent), which covers central ideas, inferences, and command of textual evidence; Standard English Conventions (about 26 percent), which covers grammar, punctuation, and sentence structure; and Expression of Ideas (about 20 percent), which covers rhetorical synthesis and transitions.</p>
    <p>The Math section covers four domains: Algebra (about 35 percent of questions), which includes linear equations, inequalities, and systems; Advanced Math (about 35 percent), which includes quadratic and polynomial functions, nonlinear equations, and exponential expressions; Problem Solving and Data Analysis (about 15 percent), which includes ratios, percentages, probability, and data interpretation; and Geometry and Trigonometry (about 15 percent), which includes area, volume, angles, circles, and right triangle trigonometry.</p>
    <p>Note that approximately 75 percent of math questions are multiple choice and 25 percent are student-produced response questions where you type your answer rather than selecting from options.</p>

    <h2>Scoring System and Percentiles</h2>
    <p>The digital SAT is scored on the same 400 to 1600 scale as the paper SAT, with each section — Reading and Writing, and Math — scored from 200 to 800. Your composite score is the sum of the two section scores. There is no penalty for guessing, so you should answer every question even if you are unsure.</p>
    <p>The adaptive design means that the difficulty of your Module 2 questions affects your potential score range. If you perform well on Module 1 and receive the harder Module 2, your score ceiling is higher even if you miss some questions in Module 2. Conversely, if you receive the easier Module 2, your maximum possible section score is lower, typically capped around 600 to 650 for that section.</p>
    <p>This makes performance on Module 1 especially important. Getting routed to the harder Module 2 gives you access to the full score range, so a strong start is critical. Use our <a href="/education-calculators/sat-score-calculator/">SAT score calculator</a> to understand how raw scores translate to scaled scores and percentiles.</p>
